### SmartWealth API Testing
### Use REST Client extension to run these requests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/v1

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Health Checks
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Root endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Health check
GET {{apiUrl}}/health

### Database health check
GET {{apiUrl}}/health/db


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Authentication (Coming in Step 6)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Register new user
# POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
# Content-Type: application/json
# 
# {
#   "email": "test@example.com",
#   "password": "Test1234!",
#   "full_name": "Test User"
# }

### Login
# POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/login
# Content-Type: application/json
# 
# {
#   "email": "test@example.com",
#   "password": "Test1234!"
# }

### Refresh token
# POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/refresh
# Content-Type: application/json
# 
# {
#   "refresh_token": "your-refresh-token-here"
# }


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Assets (Coming in Step 7)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all user assets
# GET {{apiUrl}}/assets
# Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Create new asset
# POST {{apiUrl}}/assets
# Content-Type: application/json
# Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
# 
# {
#   "symbol": "BBCA.JK",
#   "asset_name": "Bank Central Asia",
#   "asset_type": "stock_id",
#   "quantity": 100,
#   "avg_buy_price": 8500
# }


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Dashboard (Coming in Step 10)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get net worth
# GET {{apiUrl}}/dashboard/net-worth
# Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Get allocation
# GET {{apiUrl}}/dashboard/allocation
# Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
